column5: Anyone have any experience with Jemar or Samuelson lake near Nakina?
Hey phidelt157! Excellent place to check for more info! Good to see you on this and Ontariofishing.net!

phidelt157, how did your Canada border crossing go this spring? After that 200+ post thread you spawned last winter, I must have closure ;)derrek."I'll teach these eyes to see,beyond these walls in front of me"- Bruce Springsteen, "Trapped"

Ha ha......no problems at the border, in fact the guy who had the DUI backed out anyway, so no worries I guess. Thanks for the response, and sorry to keep you on the edge of your seat for four months.157
Glad to hear it worked out - hope you had a good trip.derrek."I'll teach these eyes to see,beyond these walls in front of me"- Bruce Springsteen, "Trapped"

I haven't been to either of those lakes but have been on a few other lakes that Leuenbergers run. I have had great luck on them so i can imagine that either of those would be fine. Always been happy on my trips in Nakina.Smokey
